Q1_Correct_Answer:
# Read input from STDIN. Print your output to STDOUT

def main()
	t = gets.chomp.to_i
	t.times do
		n = gets.chomp.to_i
		villan = []
		player = []
		villan = gets
		villan = villan.split.map(&:to_i)

		player = gets
		player = player.split.map(&:to_i)

		villan.sort_by! { |number| -number }
		player.sort_by! { |number| -number }

		lost = false
		villan.each_with_index do |strength, index| 
			lost = true and break if strength > player[index]
		end

		print lost ? "LOSE\n" : "WIN\n"
	end
end
main()

Q2_Correct_Answer: using System; using System.Collections.Generic; using System.IO; using System.Linq; public class CandiateCode { public static void Main(String[] args){ int n=Convert.ToInt32(Console.ReadLine()); string[] str = new string[n]; for(int i=0;i<n;i++){ str[i]=Console.ReadLine(); } Array.Sort(str); foreach(string s in str){ Console.WriteLine(s); } } }
